title: For Sale:  Regarding: FOR TRADE: EXCELLENT M1 GARAND, SPRINGFIELD ARMS
postcontent: Your rifle wasn't sent to Rock River Arms, it was probably sent to Rock Island Arsenal, as most all M1 Garands since they've been pulled out of service.  So now that that's out of the way, I wanna save you some trouble and legal woes.  An M14 is a select fire rifle which means that the ATF and the US government consider it a "machine gun" or NFA or Class 3 weapon.  What this means is that if someone were insane enough to trade their rifle transferable machine gun for your semi auto then you'd be forced to pay a $200 tax and be subject to a lengthy transfer process.  What you are probably wanting to trade for is a .308 semi auto rifle known as an M1A.  The reason I'm telling you this is that if you were to find someone willing to make such a trade, it'd likely be for an unregistered rifle and if you want one of those..... It's fine with me, I could care less but don't post it online..... I assure you the door kickers can know who you are with your cell number or your IP address from where you posted your ad.  You wouldn't want that.
